question.text: A metallic shell has a point charge <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mi>q</mi></math> kept inside its cavity. Which one of the following diagrams correctly represents the electric field lines?

solution.text: Electric field is zero everywhere inside a metal (conductor) i.e., field lines do not enter a metal plus these are perpendicular to a metal surface.
